flowRoot.flowPara: Only a stylus that's detected gets added to the list. Stylii are decoupled from the tablet, a single stylus can work on multiple tablets.
If a new stylus gets detected by proxmity of any tablet, its page gets focused/visible if the view is activated.
When the tablet view is activated and new stylus is detected, the stylus vie toggle gets a blue dot.
If an existing stylus (that isn't selected on the page) gets into proximity of any tablet, a page is not changed.
Active styluses (those in proximity of any tablet) show an "in proximity" badge
Corner case scenario you are configuring a stylus that is mapped to a different screen than the panel (with a mouse or a different stylus/tablet).
In such a case, a separate window is displayed on the other display, instead of the popover. Toggling the button closes it (it should probably have a window control close button as well).

Testing the pressure feel is done by pushing the togglebutton in the headerbar. A blank canvas with "draw here" is shown. As soon as drawing is started, label disappears. Closing the popover clears the canvas.
